@startuml traffic-flow-cold-start
!include ../../datum-theme-sequence.puml

participant "BlueField DPU\n(XDP on ARM)" as dpu
participant "Packet Queue\n(NFQUEUE / AF_XDP)" as queue
participant "Wake Daemon\n(DPU ARM)" as daemon
participant "Firecracker\n(VMM)" as vmm
participant "Workload" as vm

note over dpu: Packet arrives for\nsleeping workload

dpu -> dpu: Check sleeping_vms\nBPF hash map

== Parallel: Queue + Wake ==

dpu -> queue: Redirect SYN packet\n(hold in kernel memory)
dpu -> daemon: Signal wake event\n(BPF ring buffer)

== Boot Workload (~3-14ms) ==

daemon -> vmm: Resume from snapshot\n(Firecracker API)
vmm -> vm: VM boots

vm --> daemon: Ready signal

== Release Traffic ==

daemon -> dpu: Remove from sleeping_vms map
queue -> vm: Release queued packets\n(NF_ACCEPT / reinject)

note over dpu, vm: Subsequent packets flow\ndirectly via eSwitch\nhardware fast-path

vm --> dpu: Response follows\nnormal steady-state path

note right of queue: Total cold-start latency:\n3-14ms (boot time only).\nClient never retransmits.

@enduml
